Object.Field: OTHER EXAMPLES #1 - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - 12 Deployment Specifications

This package uses the scenarios of the mapping called "OTHER EXAMPLES #1 - IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load - 12 Deployment Specifications" to perform a full load of the partitioned table.
The scenarios use Oracle Partition Exchange to perform the full load of the partitioned table with the IKM Oracle Partition Exchange Load.
The mapping used for this package contains 12 deployment specifications, one for each partition.
This package illustrates how to use multiple deployment specifications to upload the partition table, by partition.
Data is uploaded without validation, but the upload operation is done with flow control (CKM Oracle). Constraints are disabled on the first upload operation (JAN2014). Incremental stats are set during the first upload operation as well.
Local indexes are rebuilt after every partition exchange operation.
After the last partition exchange (DEC2014), the following additional operations are performed:
1. Constraints are enabled. 2. Global indexes are rebuilt. 3. Incremental statistics are gathered.
